fundamentalists who stormed a us government center in this city 
doctors said at least five people were killed and at least 30 were 
reported injured 
the gunfire broke out when more than 2000 fundamentalist 
protesters marched toward the united states information center to 
demand banning of a novel the satanic verses by salman rushdie 
police repeatedly opened fire with rifles and semiautomatic 
weapons on the charging protesters who hurled rocks and bricks in 
fierce fighting in the heart of the capital 
