<TEXT>
the security council this week will approve 
a un peacekeeping force in namibia of 4650 troops officials 
said far fewer than the number demanded by black african nations 
after weeks of lobbying for 7500 peacekeepers african countries 
and nonaligned nations have agreed to send the smaller contingent 
proposed by secretarygeneral javier perez de cuellar 
the five permanent security council members the united states 
soviet union britain france and china had pushed for the less 
costly smaller force which is still expected to cost about 416 
million for one year 
the 7500 peacekeepers would have cost about 700 million un 
officials have said 
the black african nations contended that cutting the size of the 
namibian force would signal the population there that the united 
nations was more concerned about costcutting than ending south 
africas 74year rule over the territory africas last colony 
black african nations also feared that a reduced peacekeeping 
force would tempt south africa to tamper with elections in namibia 
in november to prevent the main guerrilla group the southwest 
africa peoples organization from winning a majority 
namibians are to election a constituent assembly that will adopt 
a constitution and organize a black majorityruled government 
in a report released friday perez de cuellar assured the black 
african nations that the permanent security council members would 
allow him to dispatch up to 7500 troops if the military situation 
in namibia warrants 
perez de cuellar also authorized the peacekeepers to carry 
weapons an exception to the normal policy under which peacekeepers 
are unarmed 
un spokesman francois giuliani said friday that he expected the 
security council to approve the secretarygenerals recommendations 
monday or tuesday the five permanent security council members who 
together pay 57 percent of the cost of peacekeeping contended that 
a peace accord signed in december by south africa angola and cuba 
reduced the need for peacekeepers 
under the accords 50000 cuban troops are to be withdrawn from 
angola by mid1991 with half of them out by november as south 
africa cooperates with the uns oneyear plan for namibias 
independence beginning april 1 
namibia is half the size of western europe but has a population 
of 13 million onetenth of whom are whites r 
